{
  "schema_version": 1,
  "contract": "material-writer-format-dialogs-composition",
  "platform": "windows",
  "definition_file": "vcl/uiconfig/theme_definitions/material/definition.xml",
  "theme_flag": "VCL_FILE_WIDGET_THEME",
  "status": "source-declared",
  "runtime_verified": false,
  "design_reference": "docs/design/10-writer-calc.md (Writer format dialogs) as an application of the shared modal tab-dialog anatomy in docs/design/08-dialogs.md and the tab-bar native part contract in docs/design/05-navigation.md -- cited by title/purpose, not section number (chapter-08 section numbers are renumbering under concurrent edits).",
  "note": "WIN-WR-003. Pins the DIALOG-notebook composition of Writer's four highest-traffic SfxTabDialogController left-icon-rail format dialogs -- Character (chardlg.cxx / characterproperties.ui), Paragraph (pardlg.cxx / paradialog.ui), Table Properties (tabledlg.cxx / tableproperties.ui) and Picture/Frame (frmdlg.cxx, one .cxx driving FrameDialog/PictureDialog/ObjectDialog via a runtime m_sDlgType string). None carry a Material paint override, so the whole Material look comes from the SHARED native left-icon-tab parts below (validated ONCE, cross-referenced by every dialog, never redefined per dialog -- identical to the parts document-properties.json/calc pin) plus the weld/SfxTabDialogController framework. Per dialog this contract pins: the modal GtkDialog + tabcontrol GtkNotebook (tab-pos=left) + reset/ok/cancel/help footer, and each AddTabPage page as source-marker presence (NO order assertion -- pardlg/frmdlg page sets are heavily runtime-conditional). Conditional pages carry `optional` and, for frmdlg's 3-way branch, `applies_when` (the m_sDlgType guard). The reused svx/cui Border, Area and Transparency pages are validated ONCE in shared_pages and cross-referenced, not duplicated four times. The real RID_M (chardlg/pardlg/frmdlg) vs RID_L (tabledlg) icon-prefix divergence is preserved exactly, never normalized. runtime_verified is false throughout: no native build, tab-rail pixels, or runtime interaction are claimed. Mail Merge (a RoadmapWizardMachine wizard, different composition class), References (Insert>Fields / Index-ToC, unverified this pass) and a dedicated Page Style dialog (factory plumbing not traced) are explicit carve-outs, OUT of this slice.",
  "definition_parts": [
    {
      "control": "tabitem",
      "part": "Entire",
      "part_attrs": {
        "margin-width": "@space-tab-inline",
        "height": "@height-tab"
      },
      "states": [
        {
          "role": "inactive",
          "attrs": {
            "enabled": "true"
          },
          "tokens": {
            "stroke": "@surface-container",
            "fill": "@surface-container",
            "stroke-width": "@stroke-none",
            "radius": "@corner-pill"
          }
        },
        {
          "role": "active",
          "attrs": {
            "enabled": "true",
            "selected": "true"
          },
          "tokens": {
            "stroke": "@primary-container",
            "fill": "@primary-container",
            "stroke-width": "@stroke-none",
            "radius": "@corner-pill"
          }
        },
        {
          "role": "hover",
          "attrs": {
            "enabled": "true",
            "rollover": "true"
          },
          "tokens": {
            "stroke": "@disabled-container",
